GILBERT VERNAM PROPOSED A TELEPRINTER CIPHER IN WHICH A PREVIOUSLY PREPARED KEY, KEPT ON PAPER TAPE, IS COMBINED CHARACTER BY CHARACTER WITH THE PLAINTEXT MESSAGE TO PRODUCE THE CYPHERTEXT. THIS LED TO THE DEVELOPMENT OF ELECTROMECHANICAL DEVICES AS CIPHER MACHINES, AND TO THE ONLY UNBREAKABLE CYPHER, THE ONE TIME PAD. MATHEMATICAL METHODS PROLIFERATED IN THE PERIOD PRIOR TO WORLD WAR NOTABLY I N WILLIAM F. FRIEDMAN'S APPLICATION OF STATISTICAL TECHNIQUES TO CRYPTANALYSIS A ND CIPHER DEVELOPMENT AND IN MARIAN REJEWSKI'S INITIAL BREAK INTO THE GERMAN ARM Y'S VERSION OF THE ENIGMA SYSTEM. BY WORLD WAR, MECHANICAL AND ELECTROMECHANICAL
